- Spoiler alert, they didn't.
- [gasps]

14:59.232 --> 15:01.401
- I know.
But I do have some good news.

15:01.443 --> 15:04.029
Klaus had a few thoughts
about the music

15:04.070 --> 15:05.280
and lyrics to your song.

15:05.321 --> 15:06.948
Instead of the chorus
how we have it,

15:06.990 --> 15:10.410
he wanted it more like
wordless Gregorian chanting

15:10.452 --> 15:12.746
over the metal screams
of the U-Bahn,

15:12.787 --> 15:15.040
so of course I said yeah.

15:15.081 --> 15:16.207
- What the hell?

15:16.249 --> 15:18.877
You can't just change my song.

15:18.918 --> 15:21.171
I finally thought
that we were on the same page

15:21.212 --> 15:22.339
about our partnership.

15:22.380 --> 15:23.840
I barely recognize you.

15:23.882 --> 15:25.467
- And that's a good thing.

15:25.508 --> 15:28.303
This was
the team's genius plan.

15:28.345 --> 15:30.764
Okay, can I be real with you?

15:30.805 --> 15:34.225
In college, I was
the king of mouth music.

15:34.267 --> 15:37.228
Der Konig der Mundmusik.

15:37.270 --> 15:40.857
But now, I'm der konig
der big fat nothing.

15:40.899 --> 15:42.484
Even you said I was a dork.

15:42.525 --> 15:44.319
Klaus can change all that.

15:44.361 --> 15:47.072
He's my one shot to make
all my dreams come true.

15:47.113 --> 15:49.240
- Well, it's your career.

15:49.282 --> 15:50.700
And if you're realizing

15:50.742 --> 15:52.619
that maybe there's more
for you out there,

15:52.660 --> 15:54.287
then maybe you should
consider the options

15:54.329 --> 15:56.623
that were presented
to you in the bathroom.

15:56.664 --> 15:57.957
- Are we still talking
about me?

15:57.999 --> 15:59.834
Because I haven't gone
to the bathroom in hours.

15:59.876 --> 16:02.545
Klaus makes me hold it
until I can taste it.

16:02.587 --> 16:04.089
- [sighs]

16:04.130 --> 16:07.092
[percussive music]

16:07.133 --> 16:14.265
* *

16:16.142 --> 16:18.436
Gisela?
Let's meet up.

16:18.478 --> 16:20.689
I'd like to talk to you.

16:20.730 --> 16:22.440
Okay, Heidi.
That was great practice.

16:22.482 --> 16:23.983
Now let's call her for real.

16:24.025 --> 16:26.528
[bell rings]

16:29.114 --> 16:30.782
- Hey.

16:30.824 --> 16:31.950
Have you seen Heidi?

16:31.991 --> 16:33.952
She was being weird
last time I saw her.

16:33.993 --> 16:35.995
- [gasps] Papa.

16:36.037 --> 16:39.332
Look, Papa's here.

16:39.374 --> 16:41.918
- You look amazing.
- Thank you.

16:41.960 --> 16:45.130
- Like my friend Trinity
from "The Matrix."

16:45.171 --> 16:46.464
- You think so?

16:46.506 --> 16:49.300
- And before
we start talking,

16:49.342 --> 16:52.470
I want to say Pieter, Thea,

16:52.512 --> 16:56.099
thank you so much
for bringing him to me,

16:56.141 --> 16:57.809
my new friend.

16:57.851 --> 17:03.189
Also, Pieter,
what a big boy you become.

17:05.358 --> 17:06.818
- It's okay.

17:06.860 --> 17:09.696
- That's literally everything
I've ever wanted to hear.

17:09.738 --> 17:11.322
- I know.

17:11.364 --> 17:12.574
But I don't trust it.

17:12.615 --> 17:14.826
- Let's walk to my vision.

17:14.868 --> 17:16.327
Bumper is singing,

17:16.369 --> 17:20.373
and then he meet
his doppelganger.

17:20.415 --> 17:22.709
Doppelganger.

17:22.751 --> 17:23.877
- Huh?

17:23.918 --> 17:28.131
- And step him over,
and over, and over.

17:28.173 --> 17:31.176
Killing his past.

17:31.217 --> 17:32.969
- What?
- Ryan.

17:34.721 --> 17:37.515
- [in Southern accent]
Howdy, do you like my stripes?

17:37.557 --> 17:39.184
I'm getting into character.

17:39.225 --> 17:41.936
- Yeah, we like your stripes.

17:41.978 --> 17:43.313
- I don't look like that.
Do I look like that?

17:43.355 --> 17:44.773
- Um...

17:44.814 --> 17:47.317
- Bumper,
are you Okay with this idea?

17:47.359 --> 17:49.527
He's condemning everything
you've ever done.

17:49.569 --> 17:51.863
- Well, it was your idea
to work with your dad

17:51.905 --> 17:53.406
'cause you didn't
think I was cool enough.

17:53.448 --> 17:56.368
And yeah, no,
I trust Klaus's vision.

17:56.409 --> 17:58.244
- Yeah, Thea, it's not so bad.

17:58.286 --> 18:00.372
Okay, sure,
Bumper's getting stabbed,

18:00.413 --> 18:02.624
but he's doing the stabbing.

18:02.665 --> 18:05.752
- Pieter, I know it's Papa,
but this is wrong.

18:05.794 --> 18:08.046
- [scoffs]
Let's not rock the boat.

18:08.088 --> 18:09.673
Papa called me a big boy.

18:09.714 --> 18:12.342
- Well,
are you a boy-ager

18:12.384 --> 18:14.427
or a manager?

18:15.095 --> 18:17.931
- [exhales softly]

18:17.972 --> 18:19.974
[clears throat]

18:20.016 --> 18:21.810
Say, Papa?

18:21.851 --> 18:22.936
- Yeah?

18:22.977 --> 18:25.814
- Maybe we should
dial this back a bit.

18:25.855 --> 18:27.148
- It is cruel, okay?

18:27.190 --> 18:28.733
You're making fun of a friend.

18:28.775 --> 18:31.027
You do this thing
where your work comes

18:31.069 --> 18:32.696
before anyone else's ideas.

18:32.737 --> 18:35.031
- Or wanting to go
to the amusement park.

18:35.073 --> 18:41.246
- You know, Pieter,
I am the most respected,

18:41.287 --> 18:45.959
most expensive artist
in Berlin,

18:46.001 --> 18:49.129
and you are an outcast.

18:49.170 --> 18:51.423
[tense music]

18:51.464 --> 18:54.342
- [sighs]
Okay, first you bully Bumper.

18:54.384 --> 18:56.970
Now you bully Pieter?

18:57.012 --> 18:58.805
I knew this was a bad idea.

18:58.847 --> 19:01.433
Come on, Bumper.
This isn't you.

19:01.474 --> 19:04.936
- Guys, I mean, come on.

19:04.978 --> 19:07.522
This is Klaus.

19:07.564 --> 19:10.066
This is the only way
I could become someone else

19:10.108 --> 19:11.192
and prove Gisela wrong.

19:11.234 --> 19:12.444
You said so yourself.

19:12.485 --> 19:14.654
Without this video,
I'll never be the person

19:14.696 --> 19:16.448
I need to be to be a star.

19:16.489 --> 19:19.451
I mean, Ed Sheeran, you guys.

19:19.492 --> 19:21.536
[tense music]

19:21.578 --> 19:24.372
- He chose me.

19:24.414 --> 19:26.499
* *

19:26.541 --> 19:29.127
Send them home.

19:29.169 --> 19:31.504
Say goodbye to your friends.

19:31.546 --> 19:33.173
* *

19:33.214 --> 19:36.801
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

19:36.843 --> 19:39.095
Goodbye.

19:39.137 --> 19:41.639
- Also, I actually drank
a lot of water today.

19:41.681 --> 19:43.475
Do you mind if I use--
- No.

19:43.516 --> 19:45.727
I told you not
to drink so much.

19:45.769 --> 19:47.979
- I'll just pinch it shut.
- Yep.

19:48.021 --> 19:49.689
[upbeat music]

19:55.653 --> 19:57.739
- I am just so excited
that this is all working out.

19:57.781 --> 19:58.990
Thank you.

19:59.032 --> 20:00.825
- Oh, Heidi, I'm so happy

20:00.867 --> 20:03.787
that you are leaving Bumper
to become my songwriter.

20:03.828 --> 20:07.457
I already feel like we are two
best friends at summer camp,

20:07.499 --> 20:10.293
exploring each other's bodies,
you know?

20:10.335 --> 20:12.671
- Yeah, it, uh--
it was a tough decision.

20:12.712 --> 20:14.756
But in the end,
like your song says,

20:14.798 --> 20:17.175
break every rule
if the rule is wrong.

20:17.217 --> 20:20.720
So here I am being wild.

20:20.762 --> 20:22.222
Whoo!

20:22.263 --> 20:23.306
I'm sorry, was that too loud?

20:23.348 --> 20:25.475
- Oh, no, I like it loud.

20:25.517 --> 20:27.310
- Okay, good.

20:27.352 --> 20:29.396
- With our two talents
combined,

20:29.437 --> 20:31.523
that newcomer slot
will be mine,

20:31.564 --> 20:33.525
and you will be offered
your paid sex leaves

20:33.566 --> 20:34.693
that I promised you.

20:34.734 --> 20:37.237
- Ooh.
I wonder who the lucky guy is.

20:37.278 --> 20:39.406
Or girl. Who knows?

20:39.447 --> 20:42.617
Well, I have jotted down
a list of 30 themes

20:42.659 --> 20:44.035
we could explore
that really push

20:44.077 --> 20:46.037
the girl power message
in your music.

20:46.079 --> 20:49.749
"Sing When You Want To" could
be the tip of the ice-herg.

20:49.791 --> 20:53.545
And yes, I said "herg,"
as in "herstory."

20:53.586 --> 20:55.380
[chortles]
- Okay.

20:55.422 --> 20:57.507
- Just a little wordplay
for you.

20:57.549 --> 20:58.925
- Yeah, wow.

20:58.967 --> 21:01.553
I, uh--
that is really impressive.

21:01.594 --> 21:03.680
And I appreciate
your work ethic

21:03.722 --> 21:06.266
and your penmanship,

21:06.307 --> 21:08.685
but I'm not really looking

21:08.727 --> 21:11.730
for, like,
song ideas right now.

21:11.771 --> 21:16.067
- Uh, what do you mean?
Isn't that why you hired me?

21:16.109 --> 21:19.863
- Well, I actually think
you might be most valuable

21:19.904 --> 21:22.907
on a more, like, micro level.

21:22.949 --> 21:26.369
Like, perhaps providing
insider information

21:26.411 --> 21:28.371
that could help me, um--

21:28.413 --> 21:31.082
[clears throat]
take Bumper down.

21:31.124 --> 21:32.625
- Oh.

21:32.667 --> 21:35.086
Well, if you have great songs,
then you will take him down.

21:35.128 --> 21:37.213
- Yes, but I don't just want
to beat him, Heidi.

21:37.255 --> 21:39.382
I want to destroy him.

21:39.424 --> 21:41.176
This is personal.

21:41.217 --> 21:44.596
He humiliated me live
on my own social media.

21:44.637 --> 21:47.640
- Yeah.
- And then Pieter rejected me.

21:47.682 --> 21:49.684
Rejected me!

21:49.726 --> 21:52.729
Even after I German kissed him.

21:52.771 --> 21:53.980
It's like a French kiss,

21:54.022 --> 21:56.441
but your mouth tastes
like sauerkraut.

21:56.483 --> 21:58.026
It's actually really good.

21:58.068 --> 22:01.780
But I just want
to stick it to him!

22:01.821 --> 22:03.990
Since he wouldn't
stick it to me.

22:04.032 --> 22:05.617
[tense music]

22:05.658 --> 22:08.953
- [clears throat]
Yeah, well, I--

22:08.995 --> 22:11.539
I don't know if this
is what I signed up for.

22:11.581 --> 22:14.084
- Oh, sure it is, Heidi.
Come on.

22:14.125 --> 22:16.002
You're tired of the way
they are treating you.

22:16.044 --> 22:18.713
Otherwise, why would you
even be here meeting with me?

22:18.755 --> 22:21.299
You gotta learn
how to assert yourself.

22:21.341 --> 22:23.551
If you don't, then--
[scoffs]

22:23.593 --> 22:26.221
Who will?

22:26.888 --> 22:29.140
- I'm super pumped
that my friends are gone.

22:29.182 --> 22:31.643
Do you think they're
eating sandwiches right now?

22:31.685 --> 22:34.604
I love sandwiches.

22:34.646 --> 22:37.357
- Time to kill
your doppelganger.

22:38.108 --> 22:41.444
- Uh, yeah, okay, right now?
Okay, yeah.

22:41.486 --> 22:44.072
It's time
to kill my doppelganger.

22:44.114 --> 22:45.740
You know,
maybe after we do that,

22:45.782 --> 22:47.659
you text Pieter and Thea

22:47.701 --> 22:49.244
and apologize,
and say you're sorry,

22:49.285 --> 22:50.495
and make up or whatever.

22:50.537 --> 22:53.623
- I don't apologize,
and I don't text.

22:53.665 --> 22:58.128
I send my messages
with an evil pigeon.

22:59.254 --> 23:00.505
- Okay.

23:00.547 --> 23:02.090
- Let us begin.

23:03.591 --> 23:05.760
[bell rings]

23:05.802 --> 23:07.929
- You can go all out with me.

23:07.971 --> 23:09.848
I stretched beforehand.

23:12.684 --> 23:14.060
- Action!

23:14.102 --> 23:16.104
- * They don't know my name *

23:16.146 --> 23:18.356
* *

23:18.398 --> 23:21.526
- Witness your old self.

23:21.568 --> 23:22.902
* *

23:22.944 --> 23:25.363
- * They don't know my name *

23:25.405 --> 23:27.615
* *

23:27.657 --> 23:30.076
* They don't know my name *

23:30.118 --> 23:32.537
- Now, kill him.

23:32.579 --> 23:34.164
[ominous music]

23:34.205 --> 23:36.916
Kill that loser.

23:36.958 --> 23:40.337
[echoing] Loser, loser.

23:40.378 --> 23:42.797
- Oh!
- Thanks, Bumper.

23:42.839 --> 23:44.424
* *

23:44.466 --> 23:46.134
- To Bumper!

23:46.176 --> 23:47.802
- Kill that bastard!

23:47.844 --> 23:51.514
Kill that loser Bumper!

23:51.556 --> 23:54.267
- Ah!

23:54.309 --> 23:56.353
Ah!

23:56.394 --> 23:57.771
- Durr, I'm Bumper Allen,

23:57.812 --> 24:00.398
and I couldn't have done it
without my team, ugh.

24:00.440 --> 24:02.692
* *

24:02.734 --> 24:04.611
- Kill him!

24:04.652 --> 24:06.029
- [gasps]

24:09.407 --> 24:10.825
Ah!

24:10.867 --> 24:12.452
Yeah, I'm not gonna do this.

24:12.494 --> 24:14.079
I can't shoot this video.

24:16.164 --> 24:17.749
Bumper's out.

24:17.791 --> 24:20.627
- How dare
you walk away from me?

24:20.669 --> 24:23.088
Good luck getting
on to Unity Day

24:23.129 --> 24:24.422
without my help.

24:24.464 --> 24:27.175
[screaming in German]

24:27.217 --> 24:29.052
- Pieter!

24:29.094 --> 24:30.720
Thea!

24:30.762 --> 24:32.514
How am I ever going
to find these guys--

24:32.555 --> 24:33.682
Hey, there they are.

24:33.723 --> 24:35.600
Oh, my God, whew!

24:35.642 --> 24:37.310
And you guys
are eating sandwiches.

24:37.352 --> 24:38.603
I knew it.

24:38.645 --> 24:40.063
- Well, if you're going
to drown your sorrows

24:40.105 --> 24:41.564
in delicious meat
on the street,

24:41.606 --> 24:42.941
Berlin is the place to do it.

24:42.982 --> 24:44.442
- Bumper,
what are you doing here?

24:44.484 --> 24:46.861
I thought you made your choice.
- Yeah, the wrong choice.

24:46.903 --> 24:48.738
I fired your father.

24:48.780 --> 24:50.115
You guys are right.

24:50.156 --> 24:52.200
I never should have turned
my back on who I am.

24:52.242 --> 24:55.829
The who I am is who got me
to Germany to meet you guys.

24:55.870 --> 24:58.707
I was so focused
on being cool,

24:58.748 --> 25:01.751
I just--
I got lost in the sauce.

25:01.793 --> 25:03.044
I'm sorry.

25:04.754 --> 25:07.966
- Well, we are sorry
we introduced you

25:08.008 --> 25:10.343
to him and his sauce.

25:10.385 --> 25:12.387
- I think deep down,
I just wanted an excuse

25:12.429 --> 25:13.471
to talk to him.

25:13.513 --> 25:15.140
Part of me keeps hoping
he'll change

25:15.181 --> 25:16.850
every time I see him,
but he won't.

25:16.891 --> 25:18.393
- Too much sauce.

25:18.435 --> 25:20.687
- He's a dick.

25:20.729 --> 25:23.023
Oh, my God.
I can finally say it.

25:23.064 --> 25:25.483
My daddy's a dick!
- Yes!

25:25.525 --> 25:28.069
- And I greatly dislike Marfa!
- It sucks!

25:28.111 --> 25:29.529
I've been there.
- Wow.

25:29.571 --> 25:31.239
Bumper, I'm impressed.

25:31.281 --> 25:34.242
Pieter never said anything mean
about Papa before he met you.

25:34.284 --> 25:36.411
- I bring out
the worst in people.

25:36.453 --> 25:37.954
- Well, it wasn't just Bumper.

25:37.996 --> 25:39.873
You had my back today.

25:39.914 --> 25:42.500
At least I have
one family member that does.

25:42.542 --> 25:44.252
- Always.

25:44.294 --> 25:46.504
Okay, not always,
but from now on.

25:46.546 --> 25:47.589
- That's fine.
- Okay?

25:47.630 --> 25:50.133
- Yeah.
- Aw, that's cute.

25:50.175 --> 25:52.177
But shut up real quick.
- Okay, shh!

25:52.218 --> 25:53.970
- Just please be quiet.
- Oh, so--

25:54.012 --> 25:55.347
- You're still talking, though.
- I should--

25:55.388 --> 25:56.806
- Quiet, just be quiet.
- This a quiet time?

25:56.848 --> 25:58.933
- Okay, could we just do
the same thing?

25:58.975 --> 26:02.312
Make up, be all cute and stuff,
but with Heidi?

26:02.354 --> 26:04.814
- Where do Americans like
to go besides the Oregon Trail?

26:04.856 --> 26:06.399
- Chuck E. Cheese?

26:08.234 --> 26:11.071
- I think I have an idea
of where she might be.

26:16.743 --> 26:19.079
- [clears throat]
- Heidi?

26:19.120 --> 26:21.664
- Oh, uh--
- Cute place.

26:21.706 --> 26:23.291
How do you know about it?

26:23.333 --> 26:26.920
- I actually told her about it
because I play bar trivia here.

26:26.961 --> 26:28.254
- Huh.
- You do?

26:28.296 --> 26:29.756
- Mm-hmm.

26:29.798 --> 26:31.341
- The other day you sucked
when we all watched Jeopardy.

26:31.383 --> 26:35.553
- Okay, well, since when
is Prince Albert a person?

26:35.595 --> 26:37.305
Anyway, Heidi,

26:37.347 --> 26:39.641
I wanted to tell you
that I finally stood up

26:39.683 --> 26:41.935
for myself, and I fired Klaus.

26:41.976 --> 26:43.853
And I should have
stood up for you too.

26:43.895 --> 26:45.230
I love our partnership,

26:45.271 --> 26:47.774
and I shouldn't have let him
get in the way of us

26:47.816 --> 26:49.484
and change our song.

26:51.444 --> 26:54.489
- While we're admitting things,
I have one for all of you.

26:54.531 --> 26:56.449
- Wait, are you the one
who's breaking into my drawer

26:56.491 --> 26:57.909
and taking little
bites out of my socks?

26:57.951 --> 26:59.661
- What--no.
- Okay.

26:59.703 --> 27:01.788
Well,
they're still out there.

27:01.830 --> 27:04.499
- Bumper, it's--never mind.

27:04.541 --> 27:06.668
Gisela tried to recruit me.
- What?

27:06.710 --> 27:08.169
- She's diabolical.
- Yeah.

27:08.211 --> 27:10.422
She told me that she wanted me
to be her songwriter.

27:10.463 --> 27:12.215
- What did you say?

27:12.257 --> 27:14.634
- To be honest,
I considered it.

27:14.676 --> 27:18.054
You know, I felt like I've been
treated like an afterthought,

27:18.096 --> 27:19.472
and you guys didn't
see me as a peer.

27:19.514 --> 27:22.100
- Oh, Heidi,
I do see you as a peer.

27:22.142 --> 27:25.061
If I was on trial for murder,
you could be in the jury.

27:25.103 --> 27:26.855
- You'd make a great juror.
- Aw.

27:26.896 --> 27:29.107
That's sweet
of you guys to say.

27:29.149 --> 27:33.319
But, no, I realized something
after saying no to her.

27:34.863 --> 27:39.409
I'm not working for Gisela
because I care about you guys.

27:39.451 --> 27:43.204
And she goes after what
she wants for better or worse,

27:43.246 --> 27:46.124
and I have been an assistant
for a very long time--

27:46.166 --> 27:47.876
and that is not your fault,
Pieter.

27:47.917 --> 27:50.295
A lot of my insecurities
came from my own fear.

27:50.337 --> 27:55.216
But if I don't take a risk,
I don't grow, so...

27:55.258 --> 27:59.888
[clears throat]
I can't work for you anymore.

27:59.929 --> 28:03.641
But do you want
to work for me

28:03.683 --> 28:05.393
and be my manager
as a songwriter?

28:05.435 --> 28:08.021
[soft music]

28:08.063 --> 28:11.024
- This is
an obvious no-brainer.

28:11.066 --> 28:13.401
- [exhales] Awesome.

28:13.443 --> 28:16.154
Yeah, shake on it, cool.
- Wait, so is that a yes?

28:16.196 --> 28:17.364
- That was a yes.
- Okay.

28:17.405 --> 28:19.074
Ah, group hug!
- We shook on it.

28:19.115 --> 28:20.575
